      "message": "[minor] Line 135: ЁЯЯб `currentCameraZoom` is a fragment-level field that isn\u0027t reset when the camera is switched by the system (e.g., when the front camera is toggled externally or when the call is put on hold and resumed). It\u0027s only reset on `cameraFlip()` and `onDestroyView()`. If the underlying camera changes without going through `cameraFlip()`, the local zoom state will be stale. Consider listening to camera-change events from `HardwareService` to reset this.",
