      "side": 1,
      "message": "[minor] Line 153: ЁЯЯб The `setCurrentCameraZoom` call happens on the UI thread inside the animator update listener, but internally it posts work to the camera handler thread. During rapid pinch gestures or the progressive animation (which fires frequently), this could queue many redundant repeating-request rebuilds. The 0.05f threshold helps but consider debouncing the camera update (e.g., only apply the last value within a 16ms window) rather than relying on a magnitude threshold, which may miss the final value if it doesn\u0027t exactly equal `end`.",
      "revId": "43a0949874ea6086ed6b0a601e3a3ebe1dff2044",
