      "side": 1,
      "message": "[minor] Line 683: ЁЯЯб On pre-R devices without `CONTROL_ZOOM_RATIO_RANGE`, the fallback sets `CONTROL_ZOOM_RATIO` unconditionally with the raw ratio value. If the device doesn\u0027t support `CONTROL_ZOOM_RATIO` at all (API \u003c 30), this key will be ignored silently. The `else` branch (crop-region path) handles this correctly, but the code only enters the crop-region branch when `Build.VERSION.SDK_INT \u003c R`. The logic is correct as structured, but adding a comment clarifying that the `CONTROL_ZOOM_RATIO` branch is only entered on R+ would improve readability.",
      "revId": "43a0949874ea6086ed6b0a601e3a3ebe1dff2044",
