      "writtenOn": "2026-05-19T18:41:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[critical] Line 725: ЁЯФ┤ Thread-safety issue: `setZoomRatio` reads `params.cameraSession`, `params.camera`, and `params.previewSurface` on the calling thread (UI thread) and then posts work using those same references on the camera handler thread. Between the null-check and the `handler.post` execution, the session could be closed by `closeCamera()` running on another thread, leading to `IllegalStateException`. You should move the entire session/camera validity check inside the `handler.post` block:\n```suggestion\n        handler.post {\n            val session \u003d params.cameraSession\n            val camera \u003d params.camera\n            val previewSurface \u003d params.previewSurface\n            if (session !\u003d null \u0026\u0026 camera !\u003d null \u0026\u0026 previewSurface !\u003d null) {\n                try {\n                    val mgr \u003d manager ?: return@post\n                    val cc \u003d mgr.getCameraCharacteristics(params.id)\n                    val availableFpsRanges \u003d cc.get(CameraCharacteristics.CONTROL_AE_AVAILABLE_TARGET_FPS_RANGES)\n                    val fpsRange \u003d chooseOptimalFpsRange(availableFpsRanges)\n                    val request \u003d buildCaptureRequest(camera, previewSurface, if (params.codecStarted) params.captureSurface else null, fpsRange)\n                    session.setRepeatingRequest(request, null, handler)\n                } catch (e: Exception) {\n                    Log.w(TAG, \"setZoomRatio: failed to update repeating request\", e)\n                }\n            }\n        }\n```",
      "revId": "43a0949874ea6086ed6b0a601e3a3ebe1dff2044",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
