      "side": 1,
      "message": "[critical] Line 734: ЁЯФ┤ Thread-safety issue: `setZoomRatio` is called from the UI thread (gesture detectors in CallFragment). It reads `params.cameraSession`, `params.camera`, and `params.previewSurface` on the calling thread, then posts work to `handler`. However, these fields can be nulled out concurrently on the camera handler thread (e.g., in `closeCamera`). Between reading `session !\u003d null` and using `session` inside the posted lambda, the session could be closed. While the posted lambda catches exceptions, the race on the outer null-check is still risky. Consider either reading all params inside the posted block, or adding `@Volatile`/synchronization on the mutable session/camera fields.",
      "revId": "43a0949874ea6086ed6b0a601e3a3ebe1dff2044",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
