      "message": "[minor] Line 142: ЁЯЯб Both `attach()` and `onTouchEvent()` provide duplicate touch-handling logic. The `attach()` method sets a touch listener internally, while the class doc says the host should forward via `onTouchEvent`. Having both paths is confusing and `onTouchEvent` appears unused (VideoSinkView calls `attach()`). Consider removing the public `onTouchEvent` method or the `attach()` method to avoid confusion and ensure a single entry point.",
