      "side": 1,
      "message": "[minor] Line 64: ЁЯЯб `setPinchToZoomEnabled` can be called repeatedly from `ParticipantsContainerView` on every layout pass (via `updateParticipantInfoOverlay`). While the early-return guards (`if (enabled \u0026\u0026 zoomHelper \u003d\u003d null)`) prevent redundant object creation, calling `configureTransform` every time is wasteful. Consider tracking the current enabled state in a boolean and short-circuiting if unchanged:\n```suggestion\n    fun setPinchToZoomEnabled(enabled: Boolean) {\n        val currentlyEnabled \u003d zoomHelper !\u003d null\n        if (enabled \u003d\u003d currentlyEnabled) return\n        if (enabled) {\n            zoomHelper \u003d VideoDisplayZoomHelper(context, this).also { it.attach() }\n            configureTransform(ratioWidth, ratioHeight)\n        } else {\n            setOnTouchListener(null)\n            zoomHelper \u003d null\n            configureTransform(ratioWidth, ratioHeight)\n        }\n    }\n```",
